ratings.comment: Chris Coe was great! He is very passionate about his class and takes his time in lectures, giving us time to take notes. He doesn't mind stopping to answer questions, which is very helpful. The class is graded on a few exams but to me, the material was very interesting and now I really want to go to Africa and work in a primate rescue center.
Dr. Coe is such a friendly and wholesome guy. Class is super easy as long as you pay attention and take notes. Clearly passionate about the topic.

Everything on the exams is from lectures even if he just randomly mentions something off-hand it'll be on the exams which is super frustrating. He is very knowledgable and cares a lot about his subject, but he speaks at about 1/2 the speed of a normal person. Honestly, I wouldn't recommend this class, but it's not the worst choice for a psych class
Amazing professor, grade based on three exams. Take specific notes during lecture. I loved this class and learned so much.

Professor Coe is awesome! i always looked forward to his lectures and if you like animals you will most likely find it interesting. He is really passionate about what he teaches. there are only 2 exams (180 q each) but they are very simple if you attend lectures and do the readings. overall an awesome prof and i would highly recommend!

Dr. Coe is the reason I became interested in environmental science and conservation. His lectures were always interesting and exams were multiple choice & not difficult if you reviewed the day or two before. If you're not a life sciences major, highly recommend as your bio credits! Honestly, I recommend this class to everyone.

3 exams, not accumulative. Tests are 130 question multiple choice. Coe is awesome, super funny and very passionate about what he teaches. He does tend to ramble a little, and his teaching style takes a bit to get used to. Take pictures of the slides because he doesn't post them. Very fun class, just have to memorize a lot for the exams

Coe is a great professor who really cares about the subject material. Tests are all multiple choice and super long but not tough. Attend all lectures and write down everything he says, he'll test you on things that aren't on the powerpoint. No slides or recorded lectures posted. Really awesome class, worth the time.
Professor Coe is a world renowned primatologist and is very respected among the psychologist department. I was excited to go to his lectures, as he presented each one in a very unique way.

I really looked forward to going to this class twice a week because it was always so interesting and Coe is an amazing lecturer. Tests are very long and difficult and are each 1/3 of your grade, so go to ALL classes and take good notes. If you put in the effort for this class, you will learn so much!!

I absolutely loved Professor Coe. He always kept things interesting and funny in lecture and was super passionate about what he does; it's refreshing to have a professor be actually GOOD at teaching. The only issue was that the class itself is only 3 exams total. Go to lecture, take GOOD notes and READ the articles and you'll be fine :)

Professor Coe is so nice and funny, and he clearly knows a lot about what he teaches. BUT, he tends to ramble to a point where I had no idea what was important to know. Tests are extremely long and difficult. A lot of questions are things he only mentioned once. His powerpoints are mostly pictures, so you need to really pay attention to lectures.

Coe is a great lecturer. I loved attending lectures. It's a power lecture twice a week but he makes them feel so short! Tests are long and you won't pass if you don't attend lectures. There are a few supplementary readings that you have to read for exams but they're pretty easy to follow. I would definitely recommend this class!

Coe knew how to engage a large lecture hall. I had very little interest in primates prior to this class and now I'm excited to learn about them! He was clearly so passionate about his work and was excited to share it. 2 power lectures a week, but they flew by. Tests are long but fair. Must go to lecture, but you'll want to go anyways!

This is a great class to take! A real college course. 100% of your grade is from 3 exams. Exams will be VERY HARD if you struggle to work quickly. 130 questions in 75 minutes. Rushes through slides, and students audibly groan around you when they can't get everything down. Take thorough notes. Get there early. Coe is great but not very approachable
Lectures are interesting, and necessary if you want to do well. Exams are 130 questions each at 1 point. There's a reader to complement lecture. Not a on of work. Great class!

Professor Coe is awesome. He is so interesting and knows what hes talking about. You get the feeling that he has done just about every kind of research. You definitely have to go to lecture but I looked forward to it every day. Tests are long and detailed but if you pay attention in class and study youll be fine. Favorite class at UW

Passionate about his research and his class. Very clear and tests come straight from lecture. Don't buy the reader unless you want more information. Side note: For those who want Honors credit, he will subtly try to deter you with a variety of limitations and criteria. Overall the class is amazing!

Beast. Really easy to follow and tests are fair. One of the few Professors at UW who you can tell actually enjoys the teaching aspect of his job and it shows in his lectures. Don't bother buying the Course Reader from BOB's, exams are 97% lecture.
I loved Professor Coe, lectures are super easy to follow and the class is super interesting. Test are extremely long, but if you memorized all the material it is super easy!

Coe is wonderful! If you are a psych or neurobiology major TAKE THIS CLASS. I looked forward to lecture every day he is so engaging and the subject is interesting. Exams are difficult, you really need to memorize everything in your notes and the reader is helpful as a review and he does ask some questions from there! Overall amazing professor.

Coe is one of the best UW has to offer. Hilarious, passionate, engaging, helpful, and inspiring. If you take his class for Honors, you will need to write a 10-page paper on a topic of your choosing which turned out to be a lot of fun! Do yourself a favor and take Coe's class. Great guy, great primatologist, and excellent instructor.

Take this class. Prof Coe is hilarious, engaging and passionate. The tests and grading are fair. I looked forward to this class every time and was never bored. My favorite class at UW so far. I wish Professor Coe was my grandpa.

Professor Coe loves the stuff he teaches, and you can tell that.  You must go to lecture, because he does not post his PowerPoint slides online.  His tests are about 130 MC/TrueFalse/Matching questions.  As long as you take good notes and study, they are pretty straightforward.

This class was very interesting and I learned a lot of facts about Primates.  You have to go to class if you want a good grade.  His tests are super long and some of the questions are very specific but most of the info he repeats a lot during the lectures.  He also tells lots of jokes which keeps the class interesting.

This class is the best, it is very interesting and Coe really makes it worth while going to class. He is really funny and tells stories that are interesting and relate to lecture. The exams are 130 multiple choice questions and very detailed but most of it comes from lecture so don't by the reader. And you get to look at baby monkeys during lecture

I'd like to have a beer with Professor Coe. He is very friendly and is always in a good mood. Lectures are interesting and contain lots of adorable pics of monkeys, as well as funny and "inappropriate" humor which makes lecture fun. He doesn't post notes online so you must attend lecture, and his exams are long and detail-oriented so take good note

This class is extremely interesting whether you think you like primates or not. Funny guy, very interesting lecturer, and very fair tests. Attendance isn't mandatory but you'll need to attend lecture to do well on exams, but his lectures make you want to go.

Coe is amazing! I absolutely loved his class! It's SO interesting and fun, I actually enjoyed going to lectures. The exams are easy if you take good notes and review them a lot. Its just memorization, but you do have to know alllll of the details. TAKE THIS CLASS!

Coe is a really great professor. Class is interesting, you get to see lots of cute pictures and hear cool stories. Exams are definitely tricky, though. Study your notes completely and remember small details - knowing the big concepts is not enough. Overall good class, just be prepared to study!

Christopher Coe is an amazing professor and this class is even more amazing!! I have literally become so obsessed with monkeys and apes. It's not an easy A but study class notes and skim through the reader and you should be fine. I HIGHLY recommend this class. I never knew how fascinating this stuff could really be.

Professor Coe is really good. He has a clear understanding of monkeys and incorporates his research into the class. This is a really good course to get a general view on monkeys, and he orgainizes it really well. I would recommend taking it.

Coe is AMAZING! Hands down the best professor that I've ever had. He is hilarious, incredibly interesting, and is always in a good mood.  He shares his experiences about being a researcher without being full of himself. Words cannot describe how good of a teacher he is.  TAKE THIS CLASS! I PROMISE YOU WILL NOT REGRET IT!!! HE'S INCREDIBLE!!!

This class is so much fun. You basically look at pictures of baby monkeys all day. Coe is really funny and nice. Exams are long, like 130 multiple choice questions, but it's basically just memorization. Easy to study for though because the material is so interesting and fun to learn. Also counts as a science credit! Take this class!

He was an amazing professor. I was already very interested in the topic but he made it that much better. The exams are long (about 130 questions) to do in about an hour, but the questions are pretty straight forward so it's not too bad. Great jokes and cute monkey pictures throughout the semester! Recommend.

Coe is probably one of the best professors at this university. He truly cares about his students interest in the course material and making the class interesting. The class itself is fantastic, even if you never though you'd be interested by monkeys. Not an easy A. The exams are detailed but not tricky if you study. TAKE THIS CLASS!
This class is great. Interesting and if you go to lecture the exams should be just fine! I really recommend this class!

Very interesting and Coe is an excellent prof. You need to go to lecture to get notes or else you will have problems on the 3 exams. I took it cause I needed a bio science and while its not an easy class I reccomend 450 for non-psych majors seeking science credit.

One of my favorite professors at the university. He's easy to listen to and is able to make the material really interesting. The tests are incredibly long, but if you pay close attention in lecture, they're not too bad. Overall, excellent class.

Coe is a total baller. This is the field I want to go into and I've had a lot of classes on the subject, but Coe ties with Dr. Strier for making it the most interesting. Study mostly from class notes and supplement with a skimming of the articles for the jist and you should be fine!
He is an amazing professor and really draws you into the subject. Go to class and study the lecture notes and you'll do fine. Take this class, I HIGHLY recommend it!!!

Prof Coe is the best professor I've ever had. The class is very fun. He is incredibly knowledgeable and clearly loves his field. His excitement about his class rubs off on everyone so the class atmosphere is great. Overall fantastic class, BE SURE to take it!

Coe is an incredible professor and clearly has an undying passion for the subject matter. The class itself was extremely informative, but the exams were long and specific. This is not an easy class to do well in even if you put in the time. Overall, take if interested in the subject matter but do not expect an easy A.

This is a good solid class for psych majors or otherwise. Dr. Coe knows what he is talking about, and his lectures are well organized. I can't imagine doing a better job giving somebody an overview of primates in every aspect. Also great east coast accent and jokes.

Coe is the man, but overall an overrated class.  Lecture is filled with material and you need to know all of it as he can put any of it on the test...fortunately, i thought the class got much better as the semester progressed in terms of interesting material..great class for animal-lovers, but definitely need to do your share of studying

Coe is generally a wonderful man with a passion, general knowledge, and love for what he teaches. That being said this course is vastly overrated. Lectures are intense with so much info, tests are long and simple yet hard. Ends up being a bunch of notes followed by encyclopedic memorization for tests. Course isn't demanding at all yet frustrating.

Great class. overwhelming with tons of info, especially in the first few lectures, but is manageable if you study as you go, don't leave it all for right before the exam. you don't need to read his text reader. interesting and fun, Coe's powerpoints are filled with adorable monkeys :)

Favorite class i have ever taken, and Chris Coe is unbelievable. He clearly knows what he is talking about. Tons of adorable monkey pictures, tests aren't easy but definitely doable if you study. Knowing the lecture info is a must, but you just have skim the readings. Amazing class overall.

awesome guy! loves what he does and loves to tell stories! very interesting class! just make sure you show up to lecture and you'll be fine. you have to know the material well for exams, but the stuff you need to know is really straight forward.

This is an awesome class. I learned alot about things that I had never thought about before. There is a lot of reading, but it's all interesting and I highly recommend this course to anyone that still needs biology credits.
best prof and class i have had so far. If you get a chance take this class, you wont regret it
Great Prof, very funny, all in all a great class. Make sure you do the readings though! Shouldn't be hard to get an A.

Professor Coe is one heck of a guy.  I felt like a celebrity was teaching me about primates, and his accent is so fun to listen to!  Never a dull moment in this awesome class -- definitely my favorite so far.  Exams are long -- must know material very well!

I think I had too high of hopes for this class from reading previous comments about it.  It was interesting once in awhile, but unless you are VERY interested in the lifestyle of primates you'll probably still yawn a lot. Exams were okay, and he's a nice guy.

Best class I've ever taken at UW. Lecture is super interesting (lots of monkey pictures!) Exams are kinda tough, but if you study the material you'll be fine... Professor Coe is amazing. I'll miss this class!

Amazing!  This class was extremelly interesting and fun.  Coe is famous in the primate world and shares many interesting stories about his career.  Extremelly nice and approachable to his students and really cares about what he's teaching.  Study well for the exams.  I will miss this class a lot.

This is a really interesting class, but he definetly tests for comprehension, not just regurgitation.  Which is good, because you actually learn but the exams are kind of hard.  Overall, highly reccommend this class.  He is also a "Celebrity" in the Primatology field.

Best class I've taken yet. Coe is very interesting and class is always fun.  Tests are based almost completely off of lecture, but they're long and multiple choice, so you can afford to get a few wrong.
fun
He can make a primate expert even out of animal-haters. I miss this class everyday!!  He's great, I recommend this class all the time to all.
Awesome guy. Love the accent. He's really friendly and very clear and really good with answering peoples' questions. The class material was super interesting. I recommend it to anyone.
Really fun class! He's an interesting prof, and his lectures are fun.  Also, you get to look at pictures of monkeys every day.  Who wouldn't like that?!
I had him for Primates and for a course on Stress and Coping. He was amazing, both intelligent and funny. Highly recommend the Primates class for anyone looking for something different and fun!
Fun stuff
Very interesting class! He is very entertaining! Must study hard and go to lecture.
awesome teacher....very interesting

awesome awesome class! definitely recommend! its not easy, you MUST attend lecture but with studying, you can get an A. great professor, makes it soooo interesting. i still get excited just whenever someone mentions something that i learned from that class. EXCELLENT!
Awesome class and awesome professor. My roommates got annoyed with how much I talked about primates - I felt like I learned a ton! Professor is very approachable and friendly.
Primates rock and so does Professor Coe!!  This is the best class I have ever taken here at the UW!!
He's a very interesting person in general and a great prof. The class is set up in a way that if you mess up on one of the exams you're screwed so make sure you attend lecture.
No Comments

Makes a class entirely about primates fun! Its my favorite class. Theres only 3 mult. choice tests, no cum. final, & no hw, but you have to attend lecture. Test questions are from lecture, not really the reader. Highly recommend the class! Love the prof!
